/*
[OVERVIEW] Admonition
Warning, error, note, hint etc. code blocks.

[INFO] Python Markdown admonition:
https://python-markdown.github.io/extensions/admonition/

[INFO] I ported for Stylus admonition from Material theme of MkDocs:
https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/reference/admonitions/

[INFO] That icons display correct, I need to use Material icons font:
https://ru.stackoverflow.com/a/770153/199934
https://github.com/google/material-design-icons
https://material.io/icons/

[INFO] I remove [dir=rtl], because personally I don’t use right-to-left languages.
*/
details
.admonition
	-webkit-box-shadow 0 .125rem .125rem 0 rgba(0 0 0 .14), 0 .0625rem .3125rem 0 rgba(0 0 0 .12), 0 .1875rem .0625rem -.125rem rgba(0 0 0 .2)
	box-shadow 0 .125rem .125rem 0 rgba(0 0 0 .14), 0 .0625rem .3125rem 0 rgba(0 0 0 .12), 0 .1875rem .0625rem -.125rem rgba(0 0 0 .2)
	position relative
	margin 1.5625em 0
	padding 0 1.2rem
	border-left .4rem solid #448aff
	border-radius .2rem
	font-size 1.28rem
	overflow auto

	&>:last-child
		margin-bottom 1.2rem

	&>.admonition-title
	&>summary
		margin 0 -1.2rem
		padding .8rem 1.2rem .8rem 4rem
		border-bottom .1rem solid rgba(68 138 255 .1)
		background-color rgba(68 138 255 .1)
		font-weight 700

		&:last-child
			margin-bottom 0

		&::before
			position absolute
			left 1.2rem
			color #448aff
			font-size 2rem
			content "\e3c9"

			/* [INFO] Generic name:
			https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-family#Values

			[NOTE] Stylelint doesn't support “emoji” generic font family */
			font-family "Material Icons", fantasy
			font-style normal
			font-variant normal
			font-weight 400
			line-height 1
			text-transform none
			white-space nowrap
			word-wrap normal
			direction ltr
